{{Infobox University |name = '''New Government Degree College''' |native_name = নিউ গভঃ ডিগ্রী কলেজ |image = নিউ গভঃ ডিগ্রী কলেজ.jpg |caption = Logo |motto = |established = {{start date|1966}} |founder = |principal = S. M. Jarjis Kader |school code = |academic_staff = 55<ref name="News Network"/> |students = 5000<ref name="News Network"/> |location = |city = [[Rajshahi]] |postalcode = |country = [[Bangladesh]] |coordinates = {{Coord|24.3691|N|88.5831|E|region:BD_type:edu|display=inline,title}} |language = [[Bengali language|Bengali]] |classrooms = |campus = [[Urban area|Urban]] |sports = [[Association football|Football]], [[cricket]], [[volleyball]] |website = {{URL|ngdc-raj.ac.bd}} }}
'''New Govt. Degree College''', Rajshahi ({{lang-bn|নিউ গভঃ ডিগ্রী কলেজ, রাজশাহী}}) is a government-sponsored independent college. It is in [[Rajshahi]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="News Network">{{cite web |url=http://news.org.bd/news/metropolitan/rajshahi-new-degree-college-faces-teacher-shortage/ |title=Rajshahi New Degree College faces teacher shortage |date= November 29, 2012 |accessdate=July 4, 2009}}</ref>
== History == This is one of the most advanced higher secondary institute in Bangladesh and one of the most advanced college of northern Bangladesh. This college was established in 1966.<ref name="nubd">{{cite web|title=RAJSHAHI NEW GOVT. DEGREE COLLEGE - 2506|url=http://www.nubd.info/college/college.php?code=2506|website=nubd.info}}</ref> Since then it has been offering undergraduate programs and graduate programs under [[Bangladesh National University]].<ref name="News Network"/>
== Academic result == The college is mainly reputed for its outstanding results in H.S.C. (Higher Secondary Certificate) exams. In H.S.C. 2012 among the first top 10 colleges to attain highest G.P.A. 5.00 it was the only college outside [[Dhaka]]. The students who passed H.S.C. from here have remarkable achievement in their professional life.
== Extra curriculum activities == The college has an organisation named Youth Writers Forum which is organised by its students.{{citation needed|date=November 2012}}
